My Project

This is my final project to reach my associate degree in Politeknik Negeri Jakarta. The project is called kwikbus, I'm with the team had decided to use the name because it's easy to remember and sounds so familiar because of a piece of hit music in the era.
The concept of the project is based on the Internet of Things. We made an embedded system to collect data from sensors implemented on the hardware then sending the data into a database and show it on the website and mobile application.
Besides reaching our degree, the other purposes of this project are to help students who want to use the bus in the local campus area. They can see the position of the bus in realtime, so they no need to worry if the bus missing and can arrange their schedule easily. The other features of the project are to knowing the availability of the seat, bus stop position, temperature, smoke alert, and total of the passenger inside the bus.

  • Client:
    Politeknik Negeri Jakarta
  • Date:
    June 2019
  • Service:
    Website
    Mobile Application
    Emmbedded System

  • URL: kwikbus

My Project

IRMA Garden is my project to complete the task of my training program which is organized by the Indonesian Ministry of Communication and Informatics in the Digital Talent Scholarship.
The project is made with the Internet of Things concept to controlling and monitoring plant growth. There are some features like soil moisture detection, air temperature & humidity percentage, ultraviolet lamp controller, and water pump that is directly integrated with the soil moisture sensor.
Like most Internet of things concept, the project work by collecting the values from the sensor and send the data into a database then show it into a mobile application. The watering system will work automatically based on the soil moisture, if it's dry then the pump will turn on and when it's come to wet the pump will turn off, so the owner of the plant no need to worry if they forget to water their plant. An ultraviolet lamp is an option for indoor placement to replacing the sunlight and it's also can be controlled directly by a smartphone.
The ease and convenience of gardening is the aim of the following project.

  • Client:
    IRMA Garden
  • Date:
    November 2019
  • Service:
    Mobile Application
    Script
    Embedded System
    Prototype
